benchmark_config.jira_title: Implement/Test API: DELETE /1.0/kb/bundles/{bundleId}/customFields - Remove custom fields from bundle

covered: Valid Request: Scenarios @TC01, @TC02, @TC03, @TC04, @TC05, @TC10, @TC11, @TC15, @TC16, @TC17, @TC18, @TC19, @TC20, @TC21, @TC22, @TC23, @TC24, @TC25 cover successful deletion with various parameters and conditions.
Empty Response: @TC05 covers deletion when no custom fields exist.
Query Parameters: @TC02, @TC03, @TC10, @TC11, @TC19, @TC22, @TC25 test with valid, invalid, missing, or extra query parameters.
Authorization: @TC08, @TC14, @TC18, @TC19, @TC23, @TC24 cover missing or invalid authorization headers and tokens.
Error Handling: @TC06, @TC07, @TC09, @TC12, @TC13, @TC14, @TC22, @TC23, @TC24 cover invalid bundle IDs, non-existent bundles, service unavailability, and invalid payloads.
Regression Tests: @TC17, @TC18 ensure backward compatibility and no regression issues.
Edge Cases: @TC19, @TC20, @TC21, @TC22 test empty, maximum length, truncated, and minimum length inputs.
Concurrency: @TC16 tests simultaneous requests for the same bundle.
gaps: Pagination: No tests cover handling of large datasets with pagination.
Rate Limiting: No scenarios test system behavior under high request volume or rate limiting.
Caching Behavior: No tests verify caching headers like ETag or Cache-Control.
Service Degradation: Limited coverage on degraded or slow responses (@TC24 only).
Data Consistency: No explicit tests for data integrity post-deletion beyond basic retrieval (@TC25).
recommendations: Add tests for pagination to verify correct handling of large numbers of custom fields.
Include rate limiting and throttling tests to ensure system stability under load.
Implement tests to verify caching headers and cache invalidation behavior.
Create scenarios simulating service degradation or network issues to test robustness.
Add more detailed data integrity checks after deletion to confirm no residual inconsistencies.
